Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of determining the intrinsic quality of a signal processing system with respect to the inference of an unknown deterministic parameter, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of the Cauchy-Schwarz inequality and the focus on the mean, variance, skewness, and kurtosis of the system model suggest that the paper may also be relevant to statistical inference (cs.SI) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the mention of different estimation theoretic problems indicates that the paper may also be of interest to neural networks (cs.NE).
